snippet.textDisplay:
Afghanistan, but for themselves, they want freedom. This paradox is what defines their approach.
I often listen to songs, and one famous saying comes to mind: "Do not do unto others what you do not wish for yourself."
This is the irony. Pakistan’s position has always been one of contradiction.
They want to impose a certain ideology on Afghanistan, yet want to live freely themselves.
Through this, I hope those in Pakistan and India, as well as the rest of the world, understand what kind of tragedy we are facing in this corner of the world.
Our voices, our struggles, and our dreams deserve to be heard. We long for a world where we are not denied the rights others take for granted."                                                                                                                                                                                                                            متن پیشنهادی آهنگ:

در دل این سرزمین، زخم‌ها عمیق است
دشمنان ما از همانجا که در خواب می‌کشند
می‌خواهند شریعت برای ما، آزادی برای خود
اما یادشان رفته، آزادی برای همه است

چیزی که برای خود روا نمی‌داری، برای دیگران هم روا مدار
این هم آهنگ، هم صدای مردم
که در این گوشه از جهان، دل در پی تغییر است

پاکستانی که در آن باید حقیقت ببیند
و هنرمندانی که برای خود فریاد می‌زنند
آیا وقت آن نرسیده که گوش کنیم به درد همسایه؟
در این سرزمینِ زخمی، بیداری دیر نیست

اگر آزادی خود را در دل می‌خواهی
پس باید برای دیگران هم به آزادی فکر کنی
در این گوشه‌ی جهان، این صدا را بشنوید
ما از یک تراژدی می‌سوزیم که تنها نمی‌خواهیم ببینید

snippet.textDisplay: I remember listening to this song when his text came, "I'm sorry mene aapse kabhi pyaar nahi kiya when you loved me so much." while I replied, "it's okay:)" even though streams of tears escaped my eyes and I was hiccupping, controlling my emotions and my tears, not knowing who to control. This song has a special place in my heart, always had, and always will have. This song keeps reminding of my best friend, that I loved truly with my whole heart, but in his eyes I was just his best friend. He loves someone else as well, and maybe, it might be a slight more than the love I've had for him. Anyway, I really hope that he's happy with his girlfriend, and god bless him with love and prosperity.
